Kingdom, Zain Saudi, Kayan, Yamamah: Saudi Equity Preview

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-04-09T07:37:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-09/kingdom-zain-saudi-kayan-yamamah-saudi-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  Saudi Arabia ’s market. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  advanced 0.4 percent to
6574.63.  Advanced Petrochemicals Co. (APPC)  : The Saudi Arabian
chemicals producer said its first-quarter profit more than
doubled to 131.1 million riyals from 52.6 million riyals. The
shares retreated 0.9 percent to 33.4 riyals.  Kingdom Holding Co. (KINGDOM)  : The Saudi Arabian
investment company and Bahrain Telecommunications Co. signed a
“term sheet” agreement on April 6 with Mobile
Telecommunications Co. to buy the Kuwaiti company’s 25 percent
stake in Zain Saudi Arabia (ZAINKSA AB). Kingdom’s shares rose
0.6 percent to 9.1 riyals, while Zain Saudi’s shares rose 0.7
percent to 7 riyals.  Saudi Kayan Petrochemical Co. (KAYAN)  : The unit of  Saudi
Basic Industries Corp. (SABIC)  expects its complex’s basic units to
start commercial operations in the second half of the year. The
shares fell 0.3 percent to 18.40 riyals.  Yamamah Saudi Cement Co. (YACCO)  : Saudi Arabia’s third
largest cement maker said first-quarter profit rose 9 percent to
180 million riyals. The shares declined 0.5 percent to 53.75
riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at   shajimathew@bloomberg.net  